text.section:
Of the 12 members:
One shall be from the Department of Agriculture;
One shall be from the Department of Business and Economic Development;
One shall be from the Forestry Program within the Department of Natural Resources;
One shall be from the Maryland Farm Bureau; and
Eight shall be appointed from the general public.

Each member from the general public shall:
Be interested in the preservation and development of agriculture and preservation of the agricultural way of life in Maryland;
Be under the age of 45 years at the beginning of the member's term;
Derive at least 50% of the member's personal income from farming or agricultural activities in the State; and
Be a resident of the State.
